At least in northern and south-eastern Sulawesi it is a lowland species and prefers smaller streams in forested habitats or at least streams with gal- lery forests, shady streams within plantations or in steep gorges. It was also found in quiet sites in rivers and tolerates a certain level of water pollution. It is absent from polluted as well as from very sunny streams and larger riv- ers. The highest population densities were observed on small, deeply shaded streams in undisturbed primary forest (
Fig. 13
).
